ExecDesc.value: Oracle Outside In CorelDRAW File Parser Integer Overflow(IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: An integer overflow vulnerability that leads to a heap buffer overflow exists in Oracle Outside-In, a set of libraries used to decode many file formats. The vulnerability exists when handling CorelDRAW (.cdr) files. Oracle Outside-In is used by many enterprise applications. This vulnerability can be exploited by causing an application that uses the vulnerable library to process a malformed .cdr file. Depending on the application, user interaction may be required. Successful exploitation can result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the affected application.
